      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12636"> </a>Fit the first key (4) on the timing layshaft.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_012301831.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12641"> </a>Locate the inner pulley (3).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_012401832.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12647"> </a>Refit the second key (4) and the washer (5).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_012501833.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12652"> </a>Locate the outer pulley (3) and the spacer (2).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12654"> </a>Apply the recommended grease to the threads of the shaft.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_012601834.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12659"> </a>Fit the ring nut (1).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/important.jpg">Important
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12662"> </a>To prevent the ring nuts working loose and consequent serious engine damage, always use new self-locking ring nuts on all
         the timing belt rollers on reassembly.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e12665"> </a>Use tool (A) no. <span class="bold">88713.1805</span> to block the pulley rotation and tighten the self-locking ring nut to a torque of 71 Nm (Min. 64 Nm - Max. 78 Nm) using the
            insert supplied with the wrench together with a torque wrench.
         </div>
      </div>
